==English==

===Etymology===
Borrowed from Greek '''ataxiā''' meaning "disorder", derived from '''ataktós''' meaning "disorderly"

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}} 
'''ataxia'''
# {{pathology}} Ataxia is a lack of coordination while performing voluntary movements. It may appear as clumsiness, inaccuracy, or instability.

